{"atom_id": "md_dmTE_ex_a038", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/TE/examples.md", "line_start": 52, "line_end": 52, "parent_section": "§TE.4.1 [Granularity of Trial Elements]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Deciding how finely to divide trial time when identifying trial elements is a matter of judgment, as illustrated by the following examples:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.3", "ts": "2026-05-07T18:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmTE_ex_a039", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/TE/examples.md", "line_start": 54, "line_end": 54, "parent_section": "§TE.4.1 [Granularity of Trial Elements]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "1. TA Example Trial 2 was represented using 3 treatment epochs separated by 2 washout epochs and followed by a follow-up epoch. This might have been modeled using 3 treatment epochs that included both the 2-week treatment period and the 1-week rest period. Because the first week after the third treatment period would be included in the third treatment epoch, the follow-up epoch would then have a duration of 2 weeks.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.3", "ts": "2026-05-07T18:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmTE_ex_a040", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/TE/examples.md", "line_start": 56, "line_end": 56, "parent_section": "§TE.4.1 [Granularity of Trial Elements]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "2. In TA Example Trials 4, 5, and 6, separate treatment and rest elements were identified. However, the combination of treatment and rest could be represented as a single element.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.3", "ts": "2026-05-07T18:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmTE_ex_a041", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/TE/examples.md", "line_start": 58, "line_end": 58, "parent_section": "§TE.4.1 [Granularity of Trial Elements]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "3. A trial might include a dose titration, with subjects receiving increasing doses on a weekly basis until certain conditions are met. The trial design could be modeled in any of the following ways:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.3", "ts": "2026-05-07T18:00:00Z"}}
